{{BLP sources|date=January 2011}} {{Expand Japanese|小谷野敦|date=December 2009}}
{{nihongo|'''Atsushi Koyano'''|小谷野 敦|Koyano Atsushi|21 December 1962}} is a Japanese scholar of [[comparative literature]] and critic.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://business.nikkeibp.co.jp/article/topics/20101202/217368/|title=あなたにとっての「結婚の決め手」は何ですか？(For you "decisive marriage" What is?)|date=December 14, 2010|publisher=Nikkei Business Online|language=Japanese|accessdate=6 January 2011}}</ref> He also has advanced degrees and [[pedagogy]] careers in [[Osaka University]], [[Meiji University]], [[Tokyo University]].
== Early life and education == Born in [[Mitsukaido, Ibaraki]] on 21 December 1962, Koyano moved to [[Koshigaya]], [[Saitama Prefecture|Saitama]], a [[suburb]] of [[Tokyo]] when he was a third grader. He spent three years at [[:ja:海城中学校・高等学校|Kaijo High School]] at [[Shinjuku-ku]], Tokyo, which had been founded in 1891 as a prep school for Japan's Naval Academy, before entering the prestigious [[University of Tokyo]] (Todai). After graduating from Todai, Faculty of Letters ([[majoring]] in English literature), his academic career further progressed. He lectured full-time at [[Osaka University]] from April 1994 to March 1999. During that time, he gained a [[PhD]] from Todai in 1997 for his work on the male psychology of love in Japanese literature in historical contexts.
== Thought == Atsushi specializes in "[[Falling in love]]s and [[Marriage]]s in the modern Japanese society".
== Literature and researches == * "Motenai Otoko - ren ai ron wo koe te" : ( The title : Always alone - beyond the "Falling in love") * "Edo Genso Hihan" :( The Contents : On the research for [[Edo period]],he is provoking and sometimes prohibiting the exceeded and inappropriate historical imaging without suitable references) * "Tennosei Hihan no Joshiki" :( The Common Sense of Criticism on the Monarchy)
