{{Infobox library | library_name = IHLIA LGBT Heritage | library_logo = | image = Ihlia-amsterdam.jpg | caption = IHLIA's reading room on the 6th floor of the Public Library at Amsterdam, The Netherlands |country=Netherlands| location = [[Amsterdam]] | coordinates = | established = 1999 | num_branches = | collection_size = over 100,000 titles, including books, journals, films, posters, objects and archives from individuals and organisations | annual_circulation = | pop_served = | budget = | director = Lonneke van den Hoonaard | num_employees = | website = [http://www.ihlia.nl ihlia.nl] }} '''IHLIA LGBT Heritage''', formerly known as '''International Homo/Lesbian Information center and Archive (IHLIA)''', is an international archive and documentation center on [[homosexuality]], [[bisexuality]] and [[transgender]].<ref>Van der Wel, Jack: ''IHLIA - Making information on LGBTIQ issues in the past and the present accessible and visible'', p 158 - 161 in: Ellen Greenblatt (ed.): ''Serving LGBTIQ library and archives users. Essays on outreach, service, collections and access'', Jefferson, North Carolina : McFarland & Company, Inc., Publishers, [2011]. [https://books.google.nl/books?id=kT4THMkDbE8C&pg=PA158&lpg=PA159&dq=ihlia+English&source=bl&ots=KyOtsPW803&sig=tbwa00otH3PyOcPy3MYSeCl5BP4&hl=nl&sa=X&ei=goXcVM_pNMyvUaO6g-AK&ved=0CEcQ6AEwBw#v=onepage&q=ihlia%20English&f=false Googlebooks]</ref><ref>Van Staalduinen, Ko & Brandhorst, Henny: ''A queer thesaurus: an international thesaurus of gay and lesbian index terms'', Anna Blaman Huis and Homodok, Amsterdam 1997.</ref> It collects, preserves and presents to the public all kinds of information in the field of [[LGBT]]. IHLIA curates the largest LGBT collection of Europe with over 100,000 titles on 1515 meters of shelf length - books, journals and magazines, films, documentaries, posters, photographs and objects such as T-shirts, buttons and condom packaging. IHLIA was founded in 1999 by merging the Homodok (documentation on homosexuality of the [[University of Amsterdam]]) and the Lesbian Archives of Amsterdam and Leeuwarden. Since 2007, IHLIA is located in the [[Openbare Bibliotheek Amsterdam|Public Library Amsterdam]].
<gallery> Amsterdam_Public_Library.JPG|Entrance of the Amsterdam Public Library, where IHLIA resides. RozeKast.jpg|Special pink bookcase. Der Eigene - Ein Blatt für Alle und Keinen - 3 March 1896 - Adolf Brand's Verlag - Berlin-Wilhelmshagen - Collection IHLIA LGBT Heritage, Amsterdam.pdf|''Der Eigene. Ein Blatt für Alle und Keinen'' (Your own. A magazine for everyone and no one), 1896 Berlin-Wilhelmshagen. First homosexual magazine. Full text. Collection IHLIA LGBT Heritage Levensrecht1940-01.png|''Levensrecht'' (Right to live), first Dutch gay-lesbian magazine, Amsterdam, 1941. Collection IHLIA LGBT Heritage. </gallery>
