{{Infobox book <!-- |italic title = (see above) --> | name = The Musician's Handbook (Revised) | image = The Musician's Handbook.jpg<!-- include the file, px and alt: [[File:Example.jpg|200px|alt=Cover]] --> | caption = | author = Bobby Borg | country = United States | language = English | genre = Music Business | publisher = Billboard Books - Imprint of Watson Guptill | pub_date = 2008 | media_type = Print (Soft Cover) | pages = 288 | isbn = 9780823099702 | oclc = 219470209 | dewey = 780.2373 | congress = ML3790.B68 2008 | preceded_by = The Musician's Handbook }} '''''The Musician's Handbook''''' is a music business book first published in 2003 by Billboard Books with the revised edition released in 2008 by Random House. Written by Bobby Borg, the book investigates the realities of the music business and is designed to help the reader understand the ins and outs of the music industry.<ref>Laskow, Michael, "[http://www.taxi.com/abouts/music-business-books.htm Music Business Books You'll Love - The Musician's Handbook]". Taxi A&R, Retrieved May 7, 2012.</ref> Borg is a former member of the American rock groups [[Warrant (American band)|Warrant]],<ref> Muze Inc. "[http://www.cduniverse.com/search/xx/music/pid/1076754/a/Belly+To+Belly+-+Vol.+1.htm Warrant Belly to Belly - Vol. 1 CD]". CD Universe, Sept. 28, 2000.</ref> [[Beggars & Thieves]],<ref>Soussan, Phil, "[http://philsoussan.com/photos/beggars-and-thieves/bearsville-studios-bobby-borg?photo=3090 Beggars and Thieves - Bearsville studios Bobby Borg]". philsoussan.com, Retrieved July 3, 2012.</ref> and Left for Dead.<ref>"[http://www.last.fm/music/Left+for+Dead #2 Left for Dead Bio]". Last.fm, December 22, 2009.</ref>
The book was written with new musicians in mind in order to provide them an industry perspective.<ref>-Sebasky, Carolyn, "[http://www.performermag.com/Archives/bookreviews.0809.php Book Reviews, The Musician's Handbook, Revised Edition: A Practical Guide to Understanding the Music Business]". Performer Mag, Retrieved May 5, 2012.</ref> According to [[WorldCat]], the book is held in 674 libraries.<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/musicians-handbook-a-practical-guide-to-understanding-the-music-business/oclc/162118898&referer=brief_results WorldCat book entry]</ref>
